## Module 9: Scale-Up Considerations

### Scale-Up Methodology

#### Geometric Similarity
- **Maintain aspect ratio**: Height/diameter ratio
- **Scale factor**: Linear scale factor
- **Power/volume**: Constant power per volume

#### Constant Tip Speed
- **Impeller tip speed**: Maintain constant
- **Reynolds number**: Changes with scale
- **Mixing time**: Increases with scale

### Non-Linear Effects

#### Heat Transfer
- **Surface area/volume**: Decreases with scale
- **Heat transfer coefficient**: May change
- **Temperature gradients**: Larger gradients

#### Mixing
- **Mixing time**: Increases with scale
- **Power requirements**: Non-linear scaling
- **Dead zones**: More problematic at scale

#### Kinetics
- **Mass transfer**: May limit reaction rate
- **Heat transfer**: May limit reaction rate
- **Selectivity**: May change with scale

## Module 10: Troubleshooting

### Common Large-Scale Issues

#### Heat Management
| Issue | Cause | Solution |
|-------|-------|----------|
| Temperature runaway | Insufficient cooling | Enhanced cooling, reduced addition rate |
| Hot spots | Poor mixing | Improved agitation, multiple impellers |
| Cold spots | Jacket maldistribution | Improved jacket design |

#### Mixing Issues
| Issue | Cause | Solution |
|-------|-------|----------|
| Poor mixing | Inadequate power | Increased agitation, baffles |
| Dead zones | Impeller placement | Multiple impellers, recirculation |
| Vortex formation | Excessive speed | Reduced speed, baffles |

#### Yield Issues
| Issue | Cause | Solution |
|-------|-------|----------|
| Lower yield than lab | Scale effects | Optimize conditions, longer time |
| Impurity formation | Hot spots | Improved mixing, temperature control |
| Product degradation | Overheating | Better temperature control |

